<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1436,654,895]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,762,787]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName box="[779,885,763,786]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatus">
<emphasis box="[779,885,763,786]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">truncatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the unique basal projection of the inferior volsella bearing very long setae.
</paragraph>
